#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:5
msgid "Verifying bugs and bug fixes in NumPy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:7
msgid "In this how-to you will learn how to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:9
msgid "Verify the existence of a bug in NumPy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:10
msgid "Verify the fix, if any, made for the bug"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:12
msgid "While you walk through the verification process, you will learn how to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:14
msgid "Set up a Python virtual environment (using ``virtualenv``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:15
msgid ""
"Install appropriate versions of NumPy, first to see the bug in action, then "
"to verify its fix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:18
msgid ""
"`Issue 16354 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/issues/16354>`_ is used as an "
"example."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:21
msgid "This issue was:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:23
msgid ""
"**Title**: *np.polymul return type is np.float64 or np.complex128 when given "
"an all-zero argument*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:26
msgid ""
"*np.polymul returns an object with type np.float64 when one argument is all "
"zero, and both arguments have type np.int64 or np.float32. Something similar "
"happens with all zero np.complex64 giving result type np.complex128.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:31
msgid ""
"*This doesn't happen with non-zero arguments; there the result is as "
"expected.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:34
msgid "*This bug isn't present in np.convolve.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:36
msgid "**Reproducing code example**::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:38
msgid ""
">>> import numpy as np\n"
">>> np.__version__\n"
"'1.18.4'\n"
">>> a = np.array([1,2,3])\n"
">>> z = np.array([0,0,0])\n"
">>> np.polymul(a.astype(np.int64), a.astype(np.int64)).dtype\n"
"dtype('int64')\n"
">>> np.polymul(a.astype(np.int64), z.astype(np.int64)).dtype\n"
"dtype('float64')\n"
">>> np.polymul(a.astype(np.float32), z.astype(np.float32)).dtype\n"
"dtype('float64')\n"
">>> np.polymul(a.astype(np.complex64), z.astype(np.complex64)).dtype\n"
"dtype('complex128')\n"
"Numpy/Python version information:\n"
">>> import sys, numpy; print(numpy.__version__, sys.version)\n"
"1.18.4 3.7.5 (default, Nov  7 2019, 10:50:52) [GCC 8.3.0]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:57
msgid "1. Set up a virtual environment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:59
msgid ""
"Create a new directory, enter into it, and set up a virtual environment "
"using your preferred method. For example, this is how to do it using "
"``virtualenv`` on linux or macOS:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:65
msgid ""
"virtualenv venv_np_bug\n"
"source venv_np_bug/bin/activate"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:68
msgid ""
"This ensures the system/global/default Python/NumPy installation will not be "
"altered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:73
msgid "2. Install the NumPy version in which the bug was reported"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:75
msgid ""
"The report references NumPy version 1.18.4, so that is the version you need "
"to install in this case."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:78
msgid ""
"Since this bug is tied to a release and not a specific commit, a pre-built "
"wheel installed in your virtual environment via ``pip`` will suffice::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:81
msgid "pip install numpy==1.18.4"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:83
msgid ""
"Some bugs may require you to build the NumPy version referenced in the issue "
"report. To learn how to do that, visit :ref:`Building from source <building-"
"from-source>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:90
msgid "3. Reproduce the bug"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:92
msgid ""
"The issue reported in `#16354 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/"
"issues/16354>`_ is that the wrong ``dtype`` is returned if one of the inputs "
"of the method `numpy.polymul` is a zero array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:96
msgid ""
"To reproduce the bug, start a Python terminal, enter the code snippet shown "
"in the bug report, and ensure that the results match those in the issue::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:99
msgid ""
">>> import numpy as np\n"
">>> np.__version__\n"
"'...' # 1.18.4\n"
">>> a = np.array([1,2,3])\n"
">>> z = np.array([0,0,0])\n"
">>> np.polymul(a.astype(np.int64), a.astype(np.int64)).dtype\n"
"dtype('int64')\n"
">>> np.polymul(a.astype(np.int64), z.astype(np.int64)).dtype\n"
"dtype('...') # float64\n"
">>> np.polymul(a.astype(np.float32), z.astype(np.float32)).dtype\n"
"dtype('...') # float64\n"
">>> np.polymul(a.astype(np.complex64), z.astype(np.complex64)).dtype\n"
"dtype('...') # complex128"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:113
msgid ""
"As reported, whenever the zero array, ``z`` in the example above, is one of "
"the arguments to `numpy.polymul`, an incorrect ``dtype`` is returned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:119
msgid "4. Check for fixes in the latest version of NumPy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:121
msgid ""
"If the issue report for your bug has not yet been resolved, further action "
"or patches need to be submitted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:124
msgid ""
"In this case, however, the issue was resolved by `PR 17577 <https://github."
"com/numpy/numpy/pull/17577>`_ and is now closed. So you can try to verify "
"the fix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:128
msgid "To verify the fix:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:130
msgid "Uninstall the version of NumPy in which the bug still exists::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:132
msgid "pip uninstall numpy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:134
msgid "Install the latest version of NumPy::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:136
msgid "pip install numpy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:138
msgid ""
"In your Python terminal, run the reported code snippet you used to verify "
"the existence of the bug and confirm that the issue has been resolved::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:141
msgid ""
">>> import numpy as np\n"
">>> np.__version__\n"
"'...' # 1.18.4\n"
">>> a = np.array([1,2,3])\n"
">>> z = np.array([0,0,0])\n"
">>> np.polymul(a.astype(np.int64), a.astype(np.int64)).dtype\n"
"dtype('int64')\n"
">>> np.polymul(a.astype(np.int64), z.astype(np.int64)).dtype\n"
"dtype('int64')\n"
">>> np.polymul(a.astype(np.float32), z.astype(np.float32)).dtype\n"
"dtype('float32')\n"
">>> np.polymul(a.astype(np.complex64), z.astype(np.complex64)).dtype\n"
"dtype('complex64')"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:155
msgid ""
"Note that the correct ``dtype`` is now returned even when a zero array is "
"one of the arguments to `numpy.polymul`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:160
msgid "5. Support NumPy development by verifying and fixing bugs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:162
msgid ""
"Go to the `NumPy GitHub issues page <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/"
"issues>`_ and see if you can confirm the existence of any other bugs which "
"have not been confirmed yet. In particular, it is useful for the developers "
"to know if a bug can be reproduced on a newer version of NumPy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-verify-bug.rst:167
msgid ""
"Comments verifying the existence of bugs alert the NumPy developers that "
"more than one user can reproduce the issue."
msgstr ""
